<br>
What I'm looking for in a motherboard is the following:<br>
<br>
Ability for 6 IDE devices (3 chains instead of the standard 2)<br>
Support for PIII-866 and higher<br>
Quality for Gaming<br>
Quality for Audio Production<br>
Quality for Graphic design<br>
<br>
I game, I do audio work, I do graphic design.  I need room more more IDE Devices (Zip, 52x CD, 16x DVD, three hard drives).<br>
<br>
Yes, I could do without the CD, but I like the speed vs the DVD and I need support for five devices regardless.<br>
<br>
The other devices I meed to support are as follows:<br>
<br>
Lexmark InkJet printer - USB<br>
Memtek Scanner - USB<br>
Iomega External CD-R - USB<br>
Soundblaster Audigy Platinum Sound Card<br>
Creative 5.1 Speaker setup<br>
NVidia GeForce2 400<br>
standard Dimms for Ram (Don't want to upgrade to Rambus as I JUST bought half a gig in Dimms.)<br>
<br>
<br>
So, if anyone has any suggestions on motherboards to look at, I'd appreciate a post here or an email.<br>
<br>
thomas.wright@mindspring.com<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance<br>
<br>
