If you want to stay IDE, there are only a few motherboards that I am aware of that support more than 4 IDE devices without a seperate PCI IDE controller.  Brand-wise, I like ABIT mobo's, but there are many good manufacturers to choose from.  Check the websites for a particular model.<br>
Make sure you have at least a 300W power supply.  My personal cheap favorite for case/ps are the In-Win S500s; they are easy to work in, and have plenty of bays.<br>
If you plan on keeping all 3 USB devices plugged in at once, you might need to grab a USB hub; not many motherboards have more than 2 built-in USB connections. <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6856>Dastin Windsong</a></b><br>
